Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I go to Page 09 of Pelvic MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'MUscles' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is enabled and preselected
And 'Characterization II' tab is enabled

When I select 'Characterization I' tab
Then 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled
And 'Localitazion' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select any muscle from 'Localitazion' dropdown menu
Then 'Proximal enthesis' radio button is enabled
And 'Proximal musculotendinous transition' radio button is enabled
And 'Proximal third' radio button is enabled
And 'Middle third' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal third' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal musculotendinous transition/insertion' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal enthesis' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Right' or 'Left' radio button
And I select any muscle from 'Localitazion' dropdown menu
Then 'Muscle lesion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Muscle lesion' checkbox
Then 'Muscular edema' radio button is enabled
And 'Muscle fibre rupture (Type IIIa)' radio button is enabled
And 'Muscle bundle tear (Type IIIb)' radio button is enabled
And 'Muscle/tendon rupture (Type IV)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Muscle fibre rupture (Type IIIa)' radio button
Then 'Cross diameter of rupture < 5 mm' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Muscle bundle tear (Type IIIb)' radio button
Then 'Cross diameter of rupture â‰¥ 5 mm' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Muscle/tendon rupture (Type IV)' radio button
Then 'Retraction' input field is enabled
And 'Wavy course of the fibres' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osseous avulsion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Osseous avulsion' checkbox
Then 'Localization' dropdown menu is enabled
And 'Intracortical edema' checkbox is enabled
